message_1:
What is the rank of the following matrix?

\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 4 \\ 2 & 4 & 8 \\ 1 & 2 & 5 \end{bmatrix}

Solve for the rank of the matrix using the row reduction method.

message_2:
To find the rank of the matrix using the row reduction method, we need to perform a series of row operations to get the matrix in row-echelon form. The rank of the matrix is the number of non-zero rows in the row-echelon form.

Given matrix:

\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 4 \\ 2 & 4 & 8 \\ 1 & 2 & 5 \end{bmatrix}

Step 1: Subtract 2 times the first row from the second row, and subtract the first row from the third row:

\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 4 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \end{bmatrix}

Step 2: Swap the second and third rows to move the non-zero row up:

\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 4 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \end{bmatrix}

Now the matrix is in row-echelon form. There are 2 non-zero rows, so the rank of the matrix is 2.
